igin, the name of an apostle mentioned in all the synoptic gospels (Matthew, Mark, and Luke) and in the Acts of the Apostles. It is an Aramaic formation meaning ‘son of Talmai’, and has been assumed by many scholars to be a byname of the apostle   Nathaniel .  <i>Talmai</i> is a Hebrew name, said to mean ‘abounding in furrows’ (Numbers 13:22)."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":0,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":9,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Bartholomew de Badlesmere was born in 1215, in Badlesmere, Kent, England, his father, Sir Bartholomew de Badlesmere III, was 45 and his mother, Margaret de Clare, was 31. He married Margaret de Clare about 1227, in Kent, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1247, in Wales, at the age of 32, and was buried in Badlesmere, Kent, England."},"et":{"1215–1247":"1215–1247","1205–Male":"1205–Surnud","1208–1258":"1208–1258","1233–Female":"1233–Surnud","1243–1301":"1243–1301","1245–Male":"1245–Surnud","1171–1256":"1171–1256","1185–1210":"1185–1210","before 1243":"enne 1243","1185":"1185","1171":"1171","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1248":"1248","1247":"1247","1258":"1258","Abt 1245":"umbes 1245","1224":"1224","1301":"1301","1256":"1256","1245":"1245","1233":"